# The bundled ECMA schemas are redistributed on condition that they stay
# unmodified (see tests/schemas/NOTICE). They ship with CRLF line terminators,
# and this repository has core.autocrlf=input, which rewrites them to LF on
# commit -- storing bytes that are not the published files, while the working
# tree still looks correct.
#
# `-text` disables end-of-line conversion so the stored blobs are byte-identical
# to the ECMA distribution. Do not remove this: the condition the NOTICE relies
# on depends on it, and nothing about the working tree would reveal the breach.
tests/schemas/*.xsd -text
